<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-07-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-07-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="642" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d642">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A4e/645</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-07-30"><hi rend="italic">July 30,
                                1926</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received September 1.]</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 687</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to enclose herewith, for
                            the Department’s information, a copy in translation of a note of July
                            17, 1926, from the Ministry of Foreign Affairs,<note n="18" xml:id="d642fn18">Not printed.</note> informing the Legation of the
                            appointment by Presidential Mandate of <list>
                                <item>Ts’ai T’ing-kan,</item>
                                <item>Ku Wei-chun,</item>
                                <item>Yen Hui-ch’ing,</item>
                                <item>Wang Chung-hui</item>
                                <item>Chang Ying-hua, and</item>
                                <item>Wang Yin-t’ai</item>
                            </list></p>
                        <p rend="flushleft">as plenipotentiary representatives to the Special
                            Customs Conference.</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">J. V. A.
                            MacMurray</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>